Angolan province of Cunene, which has had cholera activity as well. - Mod.LL]

******
[3] Cholera - Zambia (Lusaka)
Date: Tue 25 Mar 2008
Source: AllAfrica, The Times of Zambia (Ndola) report [edited]
<http://allafrica.com/stories/200803250443.html>


Ministry of Health spokesperson, Canisius Banda, has said 31 people
suffering from cholera in Lusaka are admitted to various cholera
centers in the townships. Dr Banda said in an interview in Lusaka
yesterday [24 Mar 2008] that by the close of last week, 31 patients
were still undergoing treatment at 5 centers in the capital city, the
only area still experiencing the waterborne disease.

Dr Banda said Lusaka had recorded 253 cases since January 2008 out of
which 31 people were still admitted. The 31 were admitted in Matero,
Chipata, Kanyama, Chawama, and George townships. Since January 2008,
only one patient has died at Matero Center while the rest, apart from
the 31, had been successfully treated and discharged.

--
Communicated by:
Sidi Coulibaly <sidi_couly@yahoo.ca>

[Lusaka, the capital and a province of Zambia, are located in the
southeastern corner of the country and can be seen on a map at
