[4] Cholera - Angola (Huambo)
Date: Mon 24 Mar 2008
Source: Angola Press (ANGOP) [edited]
<http://www.angolapress-angop.ao/noticia-e.asp?ID=604890>


A new cholera case was diagnosed in the past 24 hours, at the
disease's treatment center, in Huambo city, raising to 37 the number
of cases registered since 29 Feb 2008.

The municipal head of the department of public health and control of
endemic diseases, Vicente do Assuncao told ANGOP this Monday [24 Mar
2008] that although there was this increase the number of deaths
remains at 10. The source added that at the moment 5 patients have
been hospitalized at the Cholera Treatment Center, where they are
received intensive medical assistance.

According to the health director, the only case in the last 24 hours
was registered in Macolocolo ward, outskirts of Huambo city, a region
that registered 11 deaths in 2007. Vicente de Ascencao also stated
that, in 2007, the district of Huambo registered 867 cholera cases,
which claimed 43 lives.

--
