[5] Cholera - Viet Nam (Hai Phong)
Date: Mon 24 Mar 2008
Source: VietNamNet Bridge [edited]
<http://english.vietnamnet.vn/social/2008/03/774920/>


Since the 1st acute diarrhea case was reported on 13 Mar 2008, the
coastal city of Hai Phong has had 21 patients, including 12 positive
for cholera. Most of the cases are in the districts of Le Chan, Hong
Bang, Kien An, and An Duong. There are 5 people who are not ill but
are carrying the _Vibrio cholerae_ bacterium.

Officials of the Ministry of Health, led by minister Nguyen Quoc
Trieu, went to Hai Phong on Sun 23 Mar 2008 to evaluate the
situation. They visited An Duong Market, Hai Phong Water Plant, and
Viet Nam-Czech Hospital. Health minister Nguyen Quoc Trieu said the
ministry will assist Hai Phong in terms of human resources,
medicines, and chemicals to combat the cholera epidemic.

While the number of cholera patients in Hai Phong increased, Hanoi
and Ha Tay did not record any new patients last week.

According Dr Le Anh Tuan, director of the Hanoi Department of Health,
the capital city recorded 15 acute diarrhea cases, including 8
positive for the _Vibrio cholerae_ bacterium, from 6-10 Mar 2008.
Since then, the city has not discovered any new case of cholera.

[Byline: T. Huong]

